'''Kamikawa Shrine''' (上川神社, ''Kamikawa jinja'') is a [[Shinto]] shrine located in [[Asahikawa, Hokkaido]]. Established in 1883, it is dedicated to the [[kami]] [[Amaterasu]] (天照皇大御神), [[Ōkuninushi]] (大己貴大神), [[Sukunabikona]] no Ōkami (少彦名大神), [[Toyoukebime]] (豊受姫神), [[Ōmononushi]] (大物主神), {{ill|Ame-no-Kaguyama-no-Mikoto|ja|天香山命}} (天乃香久山神), [[Takeminakata]] (建御名方神), [[Emperor Ōjin]] as Hondawake no Mikoto (譽田分命), and others. Its annual festival is on July 21.

